rving. He is not alone, many people serve socialism or communism because they believe that morally it is the high ground. They believe that sacrifice for others is the greatest human activity and preach a doctrine of altruism. <br>
<br>
I disagree with philosophy completely when it comes to government involvment.<br>
<br>
I would like to further point out that the basic princples of libertarianismm makes it the most solid moral philosphy one could follow.<br>
<br>
When joining the Libertarian Party every member must first sign a pledge..<br>
<br>
&quot;I do not condone the initiation of force to meet social or political goals&quot;<br>
<br>
That means that libertarians all believe that all people should be free to make choices and not coerced in any way.<br>
The physical use of force on another being in any way except in self defense  the lowest of all human activity.<br>
<br>
This is the first pillar of libertarian morality.<br>
<br>
<br>
Last night in guild chat Spioctor Said<br>
 &quot;We dont sell to each other&quot;<br>
<br>
I was actually offended by such a statement.<br>
<br>
Selling IE Comerrece is the noblest form of exchange on this planet. It involves voluntarily giving value for value. There is no coercion and both people are free to exchange or not exchange based on there own value system.<br>
BY not allowing guildmates to sell to eachother you break down that delicate balance.<br>
<br>
I know it breaks down any incentive I have to risk my xp for any loot. It also makes me feel that if i did camp something on my offtime that I wouldnt even mention it in guild chat as it might be awarded to another who did not put forth the effort and time necesarry to recieve it. There is nothing selfish about wanting to be compensated fairly for ones time and effort.<br>
<br>
By restricting the sales of items between guildmembers I believe you will see a lot of guild usable loot leave the guild via gfay. People just wont talk about it because they dont want to appear greedy in a selfless utopia.<br>
<br>
All common wealth distribution does is destroy incentive and create black markets. IE the Soviet Union<br>
<br>
The greatest invention the world has ever seen is not the wheel.<br>
<br>
It is money!<br>
<br>
Money allows us all to exchange what we have for what we need. Without it you wouldnt have the life you know enjoy as we would still be trading chickens for vegtables.<br>
<br>
There is no nobler way to acquire something then to BUY IT. To exchange value for value voluntarily.<br>
<br>
If you want to have the strongest team then allow them to do just that. <br>
<br>
<br>
Any way to get off my eqrant of the day..<br>
<br>
Socialism or a social democracy both basically put a gun to the head of productive law abiding people ,take their wealth and hand it to other non productive people through welfare, tax subsidies, regulation, earned income credits, and social security.<br>
<br>
&quot;From each according to his ablility and to each according to his need&quot;<br>
<br>
Sounds like the need before greed eq philosophy.<br>
<br>
I have no idea how people who preach socialism can insult the integrity of a libertarian.<br>
<br>
